<div class="booyah-box col-10 offset-1">
	<div class="pic1"><%= image_tag "boardwalk4.jpg" %></div> 	
		<u><h3><a href="https://beachboardwalk.com/" target="_blank">Santa Cruz Beach Boarwalk</a></h3></u>
			<p>Located right on the shoreline of the Monterey Bay, the Santa Cruz beach boarwalk is one of the oldest surving amusement parks, and one of the many few remaining on the West Coast. Days can be spent soaking up sun on the beach or riding many of the amusement rides. The most iconic ride is the Giant Dipper. Built in 1924, this coaster is one of the last wooden coasters and has gained fame world wide. Climb the 70 foot track and take in beautiful sights of the coast before taking the plunge. During the summers when the park is open daily, weekly concerts are hosted on the beach every Friday evening.</p> 
</div>	
		
		


<br /><br /><br />		

<div class="booyah-box col-10 offset-1">
	<div class="village"><%= image_tag "village3.jpg" %></div>
		<u><h3><a href="https://www.capitolavillage.com/" target="_blank">Capitola Village</a></h3></u>	
			<p>Hidden away about fifteen minutes from the business of downtown Santa Cruz, Capitola Village is a unique spot on the water. Walk along the esplanade and discover great restuarants with spectacular views of the bay. This sweet little spot has it's own beauty. Historic train tracks run acorss the the hill above. Stand on the bridge and get a sweeping view of the water. It's the perfect place to grab some lunch and head to the beach as it's just off the esplanade path.</p>
</div>	

<br /><br /><br />

<div class="booyah-box col-10 offset-1">
	<div class="pic3"><%= image_tag "jelly.jpg" %></div>
		<u><h3><a href="https://www.montereybayaquarium.org/" target="_blank">Monterey Bay Aquarium</a></h3></u>
			<p>Located at the south-end of the bay, The Monterey Bay Aquarium is a must when visiting the central coast. Opened in 1984, this aquarium focuses heavily on marine conversation and wildlife rehabilitation. The aquarium also holds educational programs for those interested in marine ecology. Many different exhibits are offered for viewing so there is something for everyone to see and experience. From penguins to batrays to great white sharks, this aquarium works with a diverse range of animals.</p>
</div>	

<br /><br /><br />

<div class="booyah-box col-10 offset-1">
	<div class="train"><%= image_tag "roar.jpg" %></div>
		<u><h3><a href="https://www.roaringcamp.com/" target="_blank">Roaring Camp Railroads</a></h3></u>
			<p>Located in the Santa Cruz Mountains, Roaring Camp Railroads is a fun place for the whole family. Board a locomotive and enjoy the ride through the scenic forests down to the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk. Feel immersed in the grove of redwood trees and enjoy the beauty of the nature around you. You might even see a famous banana slug. After a fun day at the beach, you can board the train and head into the mountains for your trip back.</p>
</div>

<br /><br /><br />

<div class="booyah-box col-10 offset-1">
	<div class="ocean"><%= image_tag "westcliff2.jpg"%></div>
		<u><h3>West Cliff Drive</h3></u>
		<p>A favoirte spot for locals, West Cliff Drive is a stretch of coast with some of the best views in the town. You can walk/drive/or ride bikes along this stretch. Stop at the Surf Museum and learn more about the towns surf history. The iconic lighthouse sits on West Cliff and makes a great spot for pictures. One of Santa Cruz's famous famous surf spots, Steamer's Lane, is visible from West Cliff so you're sure to see some surfers catching waves below.</p>		
</div>

<br /><br /><br />

<div class="booyah-box col-10 offset-1">
	<div class="bridges"><%= image_tag "natural2.jpg" %></div>
		<u><h3><a href="http://www.parks.ca.gov/?page_id=541" target="_blank">Natural Bridges</a></h3></u>
			<p>Located at the end of West Cliff Drive, this California state park known for its feature of a natural bridge across the beach, Natural Bridges is a local favorite for beautiful sights on the ocean. The park is also a hotspot to see the migrations of Monarch Butterflies. The Butterfly Natural Reserve is home to over 150,000 monarch butterflies during the months of October through early February.</p>
</div>	


